Psychic Animal Pulser.description: A one-use broad-wave psychic effector. The psychic pulse fills lower minds with terrifying imagery, driving all animals in the region into a manhunting rage. Animals currently under your control will not be affected.
Psychic Animal Pulser.label: Psychic Animal Pulser

Psychic Soothe Pulser.description: A one-use broad-wave psychic effector. The psychic pulse induces self-satisfying perceptual distortions, giving a temporary mood boost to everyone in the region.
Psychic Soothe Pulser.label: Psychic Soothe Pulser

Persona Core.description: A hyper-advanced computer core that houses a peak-human-equivalent machine persona. In its isolated state, the core is dormant. Installed in a proper support structure, however, it can become a mind of great power.
Persona Core.label: Persona Core

Healer Mech Serum.description: A one-use super-dose of mechanites tuned to heal health conditions. The mechanites will target and heal the single worst health condition affecting someone at any given time. Works even on health conditions that would otherwise be incurable. The mechanites can even transmute themselves into organic matter, forming new limbs or organs as needed.
Healer Mech Serum.label: Healer Mech Serum

Resurrector Mech Serum.description: A one-use super-dose of mechanites tuned to resurrect the dead. Administered to a corpse, mechanites repair broken-down tissues and kickstart the body back to life. Unfortunately, the resurrected sometimes come back with brain damage, blindness, or progressive psychosis. Outcomes are better when the mechanites are administered to a fresher body. If a body is preserved, it can even be resurrected long after death.\n\nThe resurrected also experience limited retrograde amnesia, forgetting some recent memories and social interactions.
Resurrector Mech Serum.label: Resurrector Mech Serum

Techprof Subpersona Core.description: A small AI core housing a low-grade subpersona specialized in teaching technology. When used, the AI will teach you the technology you're currently researching, instantly and for free. Can only be used once.
Techprof Subpersona Core.label: Techprof Subpersona Core

Thrumbo Horn.description: A thrumbo's horn. It's razor-sharp, rock-hard, and priceless in most markets. This is a true trophy, as well as a deadly melee weapon.
Thrumbo Horn.label: Thrumbo Horn

Elephant Tusk.description: An elephant's tusk. It is very durable and valuable. While somewhat unwieldy as a melee weapon, it can still be deadly.
Elephant Tusk.label: Elephant Tusk

Packaged Survival Meal.description: A high-quality packaged meal, manufactured for use in survival situations. While it never rots, it can still deteriorate if left outside. Great for traveling.
Packaged Survival Meal.label: Packaged Survival Meal

Nutrient Paste Meal.description: A synthetic mixture of protein, carbohydrates, and vitamins, amino acids and minerals. Everything the body needs, and absolutely disgusting.
Nutrient Paste Meal.label: Nutrient Paste Meal

Simple Meal.description: A simple meal quickly cooked from one main ingredient.
Simple Meal.label: Simple Meal

Fine Meal.description: A complex dish assembled with care from a variety of ingredients.
Fine Meal.label: Fine Meal

Vegetarian Fine Meal.description: A complex dish assembled with care from vegetarian ingredients.
Vegetarian Fine Meal.label: Vegetarian Fine Meal

Carnivore Fine Meal.description: A complex dish assembled with care from meat ingredients.
Carnivore Fine Meal.label: Carnivore Fine Meal

Kibble.description: Animal feed made from mixed meat and plant sources. Humans can eat it, but they really, really don't like it.
Kibble.label: Kibble

Pemmican.description: A preserved mashed mixture of fat and plant food. Tastes bland, but not offensive. It lasts a very long time without refrigeration. Great for traveling.
Pemmican.label: Pemmican

Chocolate.description: A delicious preparation of cocoa seeds ground together with sugar and vanilla. It fulfills the need for recreation, but it is not very nutritious.
Chocolate.label: Chocolate

Insect Jelly.description: Jelly stored and used as food by oversized insects. It is smooth, rich, and fulfills the recreation need of those who consume it. Because of its unique biological properties, it can nourish almost any creature and never rots.
Insect Jelly.label: Insect Jelly

Chicken Egg (Unfert.).description: An unfertilized chicken egg. It can be eaten raw, but it's much, much better cooked.
Chicken Egg (Unfert.).label: Chicken Egg (Unfert.)

Chicken Egg (Fert.).description: A fertilized chicken egg. If all goes well, it should hatch into a chick. It can be eaten raw, but it's much better cooked.
Chicken Egg (Fert.).label: Chicken Egg (Fert.)

Cobra Egg (Fert.).description: A fertilized cobra egg. If all goes well, it should hatch into a baby cobra. It can be eaten raw, but it's much better cooked.
Cobra Egg (Fert.).label: Cobra Egg (Fert.)

Iguana Egg (Fert.).description: A fertilized iguana egg. If all goes well, it should hatch into a baby iguana. It can be eaten raw, but it's much better cooked.
Iguana Egg (Fert.).label: Iguana Egg (Fert.)

Tortoise Egg (Fert.).description: A fertilized tortoise egg. If all goes well, it should hatch into a baby tortoise. It can be eaten raw, but it's much better cooked.
Tortoise Egg (Fert.).label: Tortoise Egg (Fert.)

Cassowary Egg (Fert.).description: A fertilized cassowary egg. If all goes well, it should hatch into a baby cassowary. It can be eaten raw, but it's much better cooked.
Cassowary Egg (Fert.).label: Cassowary Egg (Fert.)

Emu Egg (Fert.).description: A fertilized emu egg. If all goes well, it should hatch into a baby emu. It can be eaten raw, but it's much better cooked.
Emu Egg (Fert.).label: Emu Egg (Fert.)

Ostrich Egg (Fert.).description: A fertilized ostrich egg. If all goes well, it should hatch into a baby ostrich. It can be eaten raw, but it's much better cooked.
Ostrich Egg (Fert.).label: Ostrich Egg (Fert.)

Turkey Egg (Fert.).description: A fertilized turkey egg. If all goes well, it should hatch into a baby turkey. It can be eaten raw, but it's much better cooked.
Turkey Egg (Fert.).label: Turkey Egg (Fert.)

Duck Egg (Unfert.).description: An unfertilized duck egg. It can be eaten raw, but it's much, much better cooked.
Duck Egg (Unfert.).label: Duck Egg (Unfert.)

Duck Egg (Fert.).description: A fertilized duck egg. If all goes well, it should hatch into a duckling. It can be eaten raw, but it's much better cooked.
Duck Egg (Fert.).label: Duck Egg (Fert.)

Goose Egg (Unfert.).description: An unfertilized goose egg. It can be eaten raw, but it's much, much better cooked.
Goose Egg (Unfert.).label: Goose Egg (Unfert.)

Goose Egg (Fert.).description: A fertilized goose egg. If all goes well, it should hatch into a baby goose. It can be eaten raw, but it's much better cooked.
Goose Egg (Fert.).label: Goose Egg (Fert.)

Herbal Medicine.description: A pack of herbal concoctions extracted from the healroot plant. It is less potent than industrial pharmaceuticals, but much better than nothing.
Herbal Medicine.label: Herbal Medicine

Medicine.description: A kit of industrial-era medical equipment. It contains basic drugs, tools for suturing and bone setting, diagnostic devices, and various pads and fluids.
Medicine.label: Medicine

Glitterworld Medicine.description: A kit of advanced ultra-tech medical supplies, probably manufactured on a distant glitterworld. It contains advanced polymorphic drugs, nanite diagnostic and healing assisters, a mini-imager, and various multi-use tools.
Glitterworld Medicine.label: Glitterworld Medicine

Component.description: Miscellaneous gears, capacitors, circuit boards, tubes, wheels, sensors, wires, chips, processors, and other electronic and industrial parts. Necessary for assembling complex machines or electronics.
Component.label: Component

Advanced Component.description: Advanced computing and energy-directing machinery, miniaturized and hardened for the most demanding applications.
Advanced Component.label: Advanced Component

Neutroamine.description: A synthetic precursor chemical. While it is useless on its own, many drugs require neutroamine as an ingredient.
Neutroamine.label: Neutroamine

Chemfuel.description: A volatile liquid chemical. Used to fuel engines and rockets, or to transmute into propellant for projectiles, or as an incendiary weapon.
Chemfuel.label: Chemfuel

Reinforced Barrel.description: A large barrel for projectile-based weapons like mortars. In order to hold the high launch pressures, it is specially reinforced and cannot be manufactured at a small scale.
Reinforced Barrel.label: Reinforced Barrel

Berries.description: Assorted berries. Nice to eat, even when raw.
Berries.label: Berries

Hay.description: Nutrient-rich grasses and shoots, harvested and compacted for storage. Hay is good animal feed, but inedible for humans.
Hay.label: Hay

Hops.description: Raw hops. A flavoring and preserving agent that is necessary for making beer.
Hops.label: Hops

Psychoid Leaves.description: Raw cut leaves of a psychoid plant. Can be refined into various form of the stimulant drug psychite.
Psychoid Leaves.label: Psychoid Leaves

Smokeleaf Leaves.description: Raw cut leaves of a smokeleaf plant. Can be rolled into smokeable joints at a crafting spot.
Smokeleaf Leaves.label: Smokeleaf Leaves

High-Explosive Shell.description: A shell filled with high explosives. Can be fired from mortars or installed as a trap. Explodes when damaged.
High-Explosive Shell.label: High-Explosive Shell

Incendiary Shell.description: A shell filled with flammable gel and a small explosive charge. Starts fires when detonated. Can be fired from mortars or installed as a trap. Explodes when damaged.
Incendiary Shell.label: Incendiary Shell

EMP Shell.description: A shell filled with batteries and antennas, for generating an electromagnetic pulse when detonated. Electromagnetic pulses temporarily disable electrical devices and mechanoids. Can be fired from mortars or installed as a trap. Explodes when damaged.
EMP Shell.label: EMP Shell

Smoke Shell.description: A shell that generates a cloud of smoke when detonated, obscuring incoming shots and preventing turrets from locking on. Can be fired from mortars or installed as a trap. Explodes when damaged.
Smoke Shell.label: Smoke Shell

Firefoam Shell.description: A pressurized shell filled with fire-retardant foam. Can be fired from mortars or installed as a trap. Explodes when damaged.
Firefoam Shell.label: Firefoam Shell

Antigrain Warhead.description: An ultra-tech warhead powered by a grain of antimatter. Usually used by spacecraft or glitterworld war machines, it creates a huge explosion and starts fires around the target. Can be fired from mortars or installed as a trap. Explodes when damaged.
Antigrain Warhead.label: Antigrain Warhead

Silver.description: This metal is mostly used as a commodity currency. It can also be used for making decorations.
Silver.label: Silver

Gold.description: The most seductive metal of them all. While it is too soft to be of much practical use, it is strikingly beautiful and never tarnishes. Millions have died in attempting to feed the endless human thirst for gold.
Gold.label: Gold

Steel.description: An iron-carbon metal alloy used for building a huge variety of structures, weapons, and machines.
Steel.label: Steel

Plasteel.description: Advanced spacer tech structural material. Plasteel is extremely strong due to its unique molecular structure.
Plasteel.label: Plasteel

Wood.description: Wood from trees or other fibrous plants. Useful for building structures and weapons. It is a good fuel for campfires and generators, and can be refined into chemfuel. In a pinch, a piece of wood can be used as a weapon or a leg.
Wood.label: Wood

Uranium.description: A dark, heavy metal. While it is best known as a fuel for nuclear devices, its extreme density and hardness also make it good for making certain weapons, armor, and ammunition.
Uranium.label: Uranium

Jade.description: A hard, green stone. Because of its beauty and rarity, jade is often used for ornaments and decorations. Its hardness and density also makes it a good material for blunt weapons.
Jade.label: Jade

Synthread.description: Spacer-tech synthetic fabric designed for making ordinary clothes. It is soft, light, strong, and insulates well.
Synthread.label: Synthread

Devilstrand.description: Fabric spun from microfibers extracted from devilstrand mushrooms. It is very tough, good at insulating, and protects exceptionally well against flame.
Devilstrand.label: Devilstrand

Hyperweave.description: Nano-fibers woven into sheets molecule-by-molecule using specialized production mechanites. While it flexes freely most of the time, it stiffens to absorb blows as they land, and is incredibly difficult to break. The secrets of its production are known only to the most advanced glitterworld cultures.
Hyperweave.label: Hyperweave

Sheep Wool.description: Sheep's wool. It provides good insulation.
Sheep Wool.label: Sheep Wool

Alpaca Wool.description: The remarkably soft wool of an alpaca. It is warm, protects well from heat, and fetches a high price.
Alpaca Wool.label: Alpaca Wool

Megasloth Wool.description: While somewhat coarse, megasloth wool's long fibers make it very strong. It is exceptionally warm.
Megasloth Wool.label: Megasloth Wool

Muffalo Wool.description: Soft, light and provides very good insulation. Muffalo wool clothes can keep the body warm even in very cold conditions.
Muffalo Wool.label: Muffalo Wool

Bison Wool.description: Thick and coarse wool of a bison. Quite warm.
Bison Wool.label: Bison Wool

Wolfskin.description: A soft furry pelt harvested from a wolf-like creature. It is difficult to pierce and insulates well against cold.
Wolfskin.label: Wolfskin

Panthera Fur.description: A soft furry pelt harvested from a big cat. It is difficult to pierce and insulates well against heat.
Panthera Fur.label: Panthera Fur

Camelhide.description: Tanned, dried, scraped camel skin. Good at temperature regulation in hot climates.
Camelhide.label: Camelhide

Bluefur.description: The furry pelt of muffalo. Recognizable by its distinctive blue tint. Good at temperature regulation in cold climates.
Bluefur.label: Bluefur

Bearskin.description: The strong furry leather of a bear. Compared to most leather, it is quite a bit tougher and a bit better at all kinds of temperature regulation.
Bearskin.label: Bearskin

Guinea Pig Fur.description: Sheets of guinea pig fur. It is delicate, but luxurious.
Guinea Pig Fur.label: Guinea Pig Fur

Human Leather.description: Tanned, dried, scraped human skin. Most people find this material horrifying. Some find it fascinating. While a decent leather, it neither protects nor insulates particularly well.
Human Leather.label: Human Leather

Pigskin.description: Tanned, dried, scraped pig skin. While a decent leather, it neither protects nor insulates particularly well.
Pigskin.label: Pigskin

Lightleather.description: Lightweight, thin leather. Probably harvested from a small animal. Not as protective as thicker leathers.
Lightleather.label: Lightleather

Birdskin.description: Tanned, dried, scraped bird skin. It is quite delicate. Without its feathers, it provides little protection from heat or cold.
Birdskin.label: Birdskin

Chinchilla Fur.description: Tanned, dried, scraped chinchilla skin. Known as an extremely luxurious and insulating fur, it is exceptionally valuable.
Chinchilla Fur.label: Chinchilla Fur

Foxfur.description: The pelt of a fox. It protects well from the cold and is quite luxurious, fetching a high price.
Foxfur.label: Foxfur

Lizardskin.description: The tanned skin of a cold-blooded reptile. Lizardskin is reasonably tough, but does not insulate well at all.
Lizardskin.label: Lizardskin

Elephant Leather.description: Tanned, dried, scraped elephant skin. While quite tough, it is a poor insulator.
Elephant Leather.label: Elephant Leather

Heavy Fur.description: Thick leather covered in a long, rugged mat of fur. Harvested from a large, hardy animal. This thick skin insulates and protects very well.
Heavy Fur.label: Heavy Fur

Rhinoceros Leather.description: Tanned, dried, scraped rhinocerous skin. It is exceptionally durable in combat, but provides little protection from weather.
Rhinoceros Leather.label: Rhinoceros Leather

Thrumbofur.description: Furry pelt of a thrumbo. Luxurious and extraordinarily durable. Used for the highest-quality crafts for its insulation and strength.
Thrumbofur.label: Thrumbofur

Patchleather.description: A weak textile created by cutting up and sewing together various types of leathers. Regardless of what kind of leather is used to create it, patchleather's irregular seams make it less tough and less insulating than any intact leather.
Patchleather.label: Patchleather

Unfinished Gun.description: An unfinished gun of some kind.
Unfinished Gun.label: Unfinished Gun

Unfinished Simple Armor.description: An unfinished piece of simple armor.
Unfinished Simple Armor.label: Unfinished Simple Armor

Unfinished Advanced Armor.description: An unfinished piece of high-tech armor.
Unfinished Advanced Armor.label: Unfinished Advanced Armor

Unfinished Metal Armor.description: An unfinished piece of metal armor.
Unfinished Metal Armor.label: Unfinished Metal Armor

Unfinished Apparel.description: An unfinished piece of an apparel.
Unfinished Apparel.label: Unfinished Apparel

Unfinished Belt.description: An unfinished piece of a belt.
Unfinished Belt.label: Unfinished Belt

Unfinished Pack.description: An unfinished piece of a pack.
Unfinished Pack.label: Unfinished Pack
